Are you preparing for the Microsoft Azure Fundamentals AZ-900 certification? Here you can get access to 6 extended and high-quality practice tests with over 200 questions to prepare for your exam.


You can use these practice tests to check your knowledge and review your Azure understanding;
Each question has a complete solution with explanations for each correct/wrong answer and link to the Azure Learn documentation;
You can retake the tests as many times as you want;
You get support by posting your question in the Q&A section;
You can access the practice tests from a device of your choice (both Desktop and Mobile).


The Microsoft Azure Fundamentals AZ-900 certification is an opportunity for people who are beginning to work with cloud solutions and services or are new to Azure to prove knowledge of cloud concepts, Azure services, Azure workloads, security and privacy in Azure, as well as Azure pricing and support.
Candidates should be familiar with the general technology concepts, including concepts of networking, storage, compute, application support, and application development. Microsoft Azure Fundamentals AZ-900 can also be used as a starting path to prepare for other Azure role-based or specialty certifications, to build your career in cloud and Azure.


Skills measured:
Describe cloud concepts
Describe Azure architecture and services
Describe Azure management and governance


Notes about the exam:
You will have 45 minutes to complete this assessment;
You should expect anywhere from 40 to 60 questions in your exam;
All technical exam scores are reported on a scale of 1 to 1000. A passing score is 700 or greater. As this is a scaled score, it may not equal 70% of the points. A passing score is based on the knowledge and skills needed to demonstrate competence as well as the difficulty of the questions;
If you choose an incorrect answer, you simply won’t earn the point for that question or part. No points are deducted for incorrect answers;
When answering most multi-part questions, you’ll receive one point for each correctly answered component. You can earn all, some, or none of the points possible for that question;
Some questions on the exam may not be included in your score. These questions are used to gather data to update and improve the quality of each exam.

